<font color="#FF0000">MONSTERS HIDE IN THE DARK</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 20  0:21:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Sparrowhawk,<br><br>
The one thing I have always been sure about is we are a result of the sum of the parts.  These symptoms for whatever malady we have must start somewhere.  A deep wound that repairs, but doesn't heal.  A hole in the armor that leaves us susceptible to collective damage.  All threaded together.  A complex set of triggers that take us back to the original wound.  The problems come from so many different directions we have difficulty locating the source.<br><br>
The demons hides behind all the other problems we face.  We protect ourselves by so totally absorbing our self that the conscious just doesn't have time.  Let the silence come or the alone times and we feel something just below the surface.  We flirt with both extremes.  On one hand wanting it to all go away and the other curious.  I didn't connect anything until Art opened my eyes.<br><br>
Some have no choice, but are occasionally violently wrenched back into that hell which leaves the wound unhealed.  The climb can be short or long, but always consuming and usually alone.<br><br>
You and I appear to be lucky, because we can visit and return at will.  The only thing I fear is that one day the path may no be so clear.<br><br>
A Mormon elder has shared with me the teachings of one his prophets on the ability to achieve forgiveness.  Although not a Mormon I find the passages refreshing and full of meaning.<br><br>
I hope we can collectively share enough to allow our arsenal of defense mechanisms add to our strength.  I see it happening now.<br><br>
Here is to the future.<br><br>
SW<br>

